			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2012</a> paper:</span><br><i>Model Transformation Co-evolution: A Semi-automatic Approach</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/JokinGarcía.html">Jokin García</a>, <a href="../profile/ÓscarDíaz.html">Óscar Díaz</a>, <a href="../profile/MaiderAzanza.html">Maider Azanza</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-36089-3_9">10.1007/978-3-642-36089-3_9</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2b.html"><span class="tagM">T2B: Evolution</span></a><ul><li> The paper tackles maintaining transformations as metamodels evolve, i.e., co-evolution as a maintenance problem.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3b.html"><span class="tagL">T3B: Transformation Languages</span></a><ul><li> The artifacts being repaired and adapted are model transformations, with explicit methods for updating them.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The approach is semi-automatic, implying tool support for detecting/adapting broken transformations.
</li></ul></li></ul>
